[thinking] **Exploring class loading**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering if I could load an adapter in a custom class loader to refresh static caches at runtime. It seems that existing Oracle/XML tests utilize isolated class loaders for this purpose. Currently, Xerces relies on a direct class approach. There might be caveats with dynamic class loading in a native image context. I'm noting that loading library classes through a custom ClassLoader in tests means class definitions are only available post-build. I need to inspect similar tests for further insights.
